&lt;Photon Technology International Inc>said it entered an agreement in principle with &lt;ML TechnologyVentures L.P.> to undertake a research and development project.    ML Technology will pay Photon about 3.1 mln dlrs over athree-year period to develop new photonic technologies withapplications in the medical field.    Pursuant to the agreement, ML will acquire warrantsexercisable into 475,000 shares of Photon stock on February 10,1988. Reuter&#3;